√To honour
Thomas J. Johnston
Of San Francisco
Who visited these gardens as a commander in the U.S. Navy
During the Normandy Landings and Later with his family
and as president of his company"»
≈In memory of
Dr Thomas Schofield
who worked in Queen Square from 2004-2010
All of old. Nothing else ever. Ever tried. Ever failed
No matter. Try again. Fail again
Fail better
(Samuel Beckett)"Œ
ÀThis Bench and the Golden Roses planted either side of
the Gardener's Hut are to commemorate the work of
JOHN SPEED
the Gardener in Golden Square and
Leicester Square Gardens who died in October 2002"—
